ALT=""><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>

A barber may be black, but not as a barber. His blackness has nothing 
to do with his trade. 'Black barber' is an accidental predication, 
inasmuch as blackness and hair-cutting happen in this case both to be 
attributes of the same subject.

